    <p>Poetry Is A Form Of Creative Expression That Comes In Many Different Forms And Styles. Here Are Some Of The Most
      Common Types Of Poems:</p>
    <h3>Acrostic Poem -&nbsp;</h3>
    <p>This Type Of Poem Spells Out A Word Or Phrase Vertically, And Then Uses Each Letter As The First Letter Of A Line
      In The Poem.</p>
    <h3>Love Poem -</h3>
    <p>&nbsp;As The Name Suggests, This Type Of Poem Is About Love Or Romantic Relationships. Love Poems Can Be Written
      In Various Styles And Forms, But They Usually Express Strong Emotions And Feelings.</p>
    <h3>Random Poem -&nbsp;</h3>
    <p>This Type Of Poem Is Created By Generating Words Or Phrases Randomly And Then Arranging Them Into A Coherent
      Structure. The Result Can Be Surprising And Often Surreal.</p>
    <h3>Rhyming Poem -</h3>
    <p>&nbsp;This Type Of Poem Uses Words That Have The Same Or Similar Sounds At The End Of Each Line. Rhyming Poems
      Can Be Playful, Humorous, Or Serious, Depending On The Tone And Subject Matter.</p>
    <h3>Free Verse Poem -&nbsp;</h3>
    <p>This Type Of Poem Does Not Follow A Strict Rhyme Scheme Or Meter. Instead, It Relies On The Natural Rhythms Of
      Language And The Poet&apos;s Creativity To Create A Unique And Expressive Piece.</p>
    <h3>Sonnet -&nbsp;</h3>
    <p>This Type Of Poem Is A 14-Line Poem That Follows A Strict Rhyme Scheme And Meter. Sonnets Are Often Used To
      Express Love Or Other Strong Emotions, And They Can Be Challenging To Write Due To Their Structure And Form.</p>
